        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 24 at 8:18PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 818 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles east of Glazier, or 13 miles northeast of Canadian, moving
north at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lipscomb and Higgins.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
